      "widgets_values": [
        "@image1 as the first frame defining the character’s face, @image2 defining the full body, tattoos, and clothing to be maintained exactly consistent, @image3 as the coastal environment, and @image4 as the exact reference for the object that will materialize in hand; 0–2s: wide cinematic shot of the beach from @image3, soft golden-hour light reflecting across wet sand and shallow water, waves rolling naturally with foam and subtle wind ripples, the character enters frame from the left walking slowly and deliberately, full body visible, wet clothing heavy and clinging with realistic fabric folds, tone grounded and calm; 2–4s: cut to a medium frontal tracking shot, camera smoothly dollying backward as the character approaches, face from @image1 detailed with damp skin and strands of hair stuck to forehead and cheeks, tattoos from @image2 visible with a slight wet sheen, breathing steady, gaze focused forward, no stylized effects yet, only natural light and environment; 4–6s: cut to a low angle side shot focused on the legs and feet, steps pressing into wet sand, water pooling into fresh footprints, droplets falling from clothing and fingers, tactile realism emphasized with sand grains, reflections, and subtle splashes; 6–8s: cut to a medium shot from the front as the character slows and stops, shoulders rising slightly with breath, he looks down at his hand, then begins to extend one arm forward, palm opening slowly, fingers spreading with slight tension, anticipation building, environment remains still and grounded; 8–10s: cut to a tight close-up of the hand, palm fully open toward camera, a faint green particle glow begins forming directly in the center of the palm, no external vortex, particles appear like fine luminous dust emerging from within, swirling gently with controlled motion, soft green light reflecting on wet skin and highlighting pores, droplets, and micro textures; 10–12s: the green energy intensifies, particles spiraling tighter and brighter, forming a dense core in the palm, subtle vibration in the fingers as if reacting to energy, lighting becomes more contrasty with green reflections across knuckles and wrist, the shape of the object begins to silhouette within the particles; 12–13.5s: extreme close-up as the energy collapses inward and solidifies into the object from @image4, a small glass container with metallic lid and chain, materials highly realistic—thick glass with internal reflections, slight imperfections, condensation forming instantly on the surface, chain resting naturally across the fingers with weight and gravity; 13.5–15s: final lingering macro close-up of the object in hand, camera slowly pushing in, green glow fading completely leaving only natural light reflections, droplets sliding along the glass and skin, tiny sand grains stuck to the fingers, background softly blurred ocean and cliffs from @image3, the character’s hand steadies, ending on a hyper-real, tactile final frame focused entirely on the object.",
